content: Apollo 11 blasts off from Launch Pad 39A at Cape Kennedy
Spacecraft is reported 22,000 nautical miles from Earth and traveling at 12,914 feet per second
Bolt 1 released, 12.5 turns to release
Critical loss of signal to intermediary satellite, connection regained after 5.05 seconds
Flight controller 3 reaching 75.6 degrees (warning zone)
(Critical) Radio Failed
The spacecraft is 37 nautical miles high, downrange 61 nautical miles and traveling at 9,300 feet per second or about 6,340 miles per hour
Radio connection restored after 10.32 seconds @NiklasB#20211003151126
Pizza is available in the staffroom for all groundstation employees
The landing craft is jettisoned.
Collins fires the command ship's rockets and moves about two miles away.
Warning: oxygen-hydrogen mix in propulsion chamber 3 engine 2 reaching low levels (30% mix)
Midcourse correction is made with a three-second burn
@ManchuY#20211003215903 Thanks, I'll be heading down now. I hope there's still some pepperoni left
The landing craft is separated from the command module
Warning - landing craft is on its way down to the lunar surface
Spacecraft splashes down 825 nautical miles southwest of Honolulu
Preparing the ship for launching
Making a preliminary collection of soil samples close to the landing craft
23 minutes away from the LOI (Lunar Orbit Insertion) burn
